            .section#section-aboutus
                .aboutus
                    h2
                        i.icon.heart
                        | About us
                    .aboutus-content
                        p Cam and JoJo met in Bangalore, India in 2006. They had been sent as part of the graduate program for ThoughtWorks; Cam from the Sydney Office, JoJo from London.
                        p After finding each other and enjoying two months exploring India and getting to know one another, they decided (after Cam consulting his mum) to give long distance a go. The next six months were a blur of early morning skyping sessions, texting, emailing and surprise snail mail. JoJo will always treasure the kangaroo balls bottle opener that Cam so romantically sent her!
                        p They had no idea when they would next be able to see each other, and eventually JoJo decided to take matters into her own hands and booked a holiday to Sydney. Shortly after booking, TW had an influx of work in the Sydney Office and gave JoJo the option to go over on assignment for three months. This was met with a resounding yes from JoJo, who still headed over for a holiday with Cam.
                        p Luckily he was still just as handsome as she had thought, but WAAAAY taller than she remembered. They had a great trip and JoJo headed home to pack up her life to head over to Aus for a while. Three and a half years later, they both returned to London, where they met some great friends and made some fabulous memories in Europe.
                        p All too soon it was time to return to Sydney, and it was here, in a tiny pre-decorated photobooth in Broadway Shopping Centre that Cam decided to propose to JoJo in April of 2013.
